Definition: a form of neuropathy that can begin between childhood and young adulthood
Example: characterized by weakness and atrophy of the muscles of the hands and lower legs; progression is slow and individuals affected can have a normal life span; inheritance is X-linked recessive or X-linked dominant
Synonyms: hereditary_motor_and_sensory_neuropathy, neuropathy, a, form, of, that, can, begin, between, childhood, and, young, adulthood, characterized, by, weakness, atrophy, the, muscles, hands, lower, legs, progression, is, slow, individuals, affected, have, normal, life, span, inheritance, X-linked, recessive, or, dominant
Category: noun.state
